cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This is the most likely category as the paper is specifically focused on modelling the Internet topology at the Autonomous Systems level. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the hierarchical structure of the Internet, which can be considered a social network, and also mentions the rich-club phenomenon, which is a concept from social network analysis. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a model for the growth of the Internet topology, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the degree distribution of the AS graph, which is a fundamental concept in graph theory and can be related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper mentions the joint growth of new nodes and new links, which can be seen as an information-theoretic problem.
